The article states that John Brennan, the Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, is traveling to Sudan, Saudi Arabia, and the United Arab Emirates at the request of the President. In Sudan, Brennan met with government officials to discuss the implementation of the Comprehensive Peace Agreement and the status of Sudan's inclusion on the State Sponsors of Terrorism list. He also expressed President Obama's concern over the presence of Sudanese Armed Forces in Abyei and urged a peaceful resolution to the crisis. In Saudi Arabia and the UAE, Brennan will discuss options to address the deteriorating situation in Yemen, condemning recent clashes and violence against peaceful demonstrators. The article emphasizes the President's commitment to a peaceful resolution of the issues in the region.